ZCZC GE18
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
TUESDAY TO FRIDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND COASTGUARD AGENCY
AT 022300 UTC
A LARGE AND COMPLEX SLOW MOV LOW 995 OVER THE SERN NORWEGIAN SEA EXTENDS
A TROUGH S OVER THE BRITISH ISLES DURING TUESDAY. THIS TROUGH CLEARS E EARLY
WEDNESDAY WHILE THE LOW GRADUALLY FILLS AND MOVS S DURING WEDNESDAY. THIS
BROAD SLOW MOV LOW LIES W OF BAILEY AND ROCKALL WHILE A SECONDARY LOW DEVELOPS
IN THE ENGLISH CHANNEL LATE WEDNESDAY. THIS SECONDARY LOW TRACKS NE AND FILLS
OVER THE SERN N SEA EARLY THURSDAY AS HIGH PRESSURE OVER BISCAY STRETCHES
A RIDGE NE. THE HIGH DRIFTS OVER FRANCE AND THEN OVER THE LOW COUNTRIES ON
FRIDAY WHILE CONTINUING TO STRETCH A RIDGE ACROSS THE N SEA. MEANWHILE THE
LOW W OF ROCKALL AND SHANNON EXTENDS TROUGHS ACROSS THE WERN BRITISH ISLES.
NO STRG WINDS OR GALES ARE EXP DURING THE FCST PERIOD. NO EXTENSIVE FOG IS
LIKELY ACROSS THE AREA
